female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"136896"},{"n":"Owen Thomas Farnworth","p":"Labour Party","v":561,"r":9,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"136895"},{"n":"Andrea Marie Blake","p":"Independent","v":237,"r":10,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"136891","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/136891/98a0738f-438c-4b34-b514-fa8ab5ad9e19.png","stmt":"No party politics \nLocal politics for local people and local issues.\nBorn and raised in haydock all my life.\nHappy to be called a yicker.\n\nMum and nanna\n\nI want whats best for Haydock and will take on every issue of complaint from my constituents if elected."},{"n":"Ian Samuel Sutton","p":"Independent","v":229,"r":11,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"136898"},{"n":"Melanie Ann Marie Lee","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":181,"r":12,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"13993","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/13993/aebdc5f7-faac-4524-801f-ee778ce3f327.png"}]},{"ward":"Moss Bank","seats":3,"turnout_pct":null,"results_url":"https://news.sthelens.gov.uk/localelection2026","candidates":[{"n":"Gary Edgerton","p":"Reform UK","v":1664,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"137456"},{"n":"David Kent","p":"Reform UK","v":1638,"r":2,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"137457"},{"n":"Jack Thomas Styles","p":"Reform UK","v":1613,"r":3,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"137458"},{"n":"Jeanette Susan Banks","p":"Labour Party","v":1172,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"54445","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/54445/1c155845-b3dd-401a-b99e-fe439db20935.png"},{"n":"Tracy Dickinson","p":"Labour Party","v":1126,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"77408","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/77408/79335c87-974f-4389-985c-d982d41bc84d.png","tw":"\"TracyMossBank\""},{"n":"Shana Begum","p":"Labour Party","v":1116,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"125403","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/125403/e0a10283-3627-4b9b-9b42-3ed7ac9defe7.png"},{"n":"Allan John Kayll","p":"Green Party","v":605,"r":7,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"126026","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/126026/08fdf609-9383-4ac1-a912-18fb8fc6562d.png","stmt":"An environmentalist passionate about protecting nature, enhancing public spaces, doing the right thing and fighting the rise of fascism, racism and corruption."},{"n":"Lisa Cunliffe","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":280,"r":8,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"54440"}]},{"ward":"Newton-le-Willows East","seats":3,"turnout_pct":null,"results_url":"https://news.sthelens.gov.uk/localelection2026","candidates":[{"n":"Keith Anthony Laird","p":"Labour Party","v":1293,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"42171"},{"n":"George Woodward","p":"Reform UK","v":1248,"r":2,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"116152","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/116152/0fb0c993-2440-4701-926a-1df436935fc6.png","stmt":"I’m the quintessential Briton - born in Oxfordshire; spent the first few years of my life in London; then grew up in central Scotland before moving to Glasgow for university. I then moved back to England for work three years ago and now live in Newton. My ancestors are from all over Britain - two of my great grandparents came from Hartford, Cheshire.\n\nAt university I studied mechanical engineering; I enjoyed the research-focused parts of the course the most, so I stayed on to do my doctorate too. I primarily studied metallurgy, and conducted research on the crystallographic phases of ferrous alloys for industrial engineering applications.\n\nIn my spare time I enjoy amateur photography (Pennington Flash - excellent) and play drums decently enough - for which I grew up playing heavy metal but also enjoy some jazz!\n\nI’ve always been interested in politics, and have been through the complete spectrum of political leanings, being more liberal in my teenage years but more right-leaning as I grew up (as is common to do so).\n\nI’m a firm believer in British sovereignty - I voted leave in 2016 and then supported the Brexit party in the European elections in 2019, before then voting for Boris for the first time in the 2019 General because I believed he would get Brexit over the line (ouch). Democracy is important to me - I believe that referenda are good things - let the people have a say!\n\nI joined Reform in 2023 after feeling betrayed by the Tories - Brexit in name only, mass immigration, highest taxes ever, mass invasion of illegals coming across the channel, and an NHS that has ground to a halt. I chose to stand in the Leigh & Atherton constituency because it’s on my doorstep and has been tremendously let down by successive Tory and Labour governments, with a perpetual Labour-controlled council that takes its voters for granted (good in-roads being made by independent candidates!).\n\nGreen space is incredibly important to me - probably as a result of growing up in rural Scot","tw":"\"Reformukleigh\""},{"n":"Ian Francis Mills","p":"Labour Party","v":1183,"r":3,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"125412"},{"n":"John David Murphy","p":"Reform UK","v":1083,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"135495"},{"n":"Tom Middleton-Leonard","p":"Newton-le-Willows Independents","v":1055,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"125515","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/125515/448449c7-399b-46e5-80f2-714eb26ddc64.png"},{"n":"John Henry Owen","p":"Reform UK","v":1019,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"135496"},{"n":"Chris Kennedy","p":"Green Party","v":1000,"r":7,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"124915","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/124915/5017e659-613f-4a3e-8336-477229541523.png"},{"n":"Lisa Kathleen Preston","p":"Labour Party","v":993,"r":8,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"41881","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/41881/b90231eb-be7a-4d90-88b9-621034492f85.png"},{"n":"David Smith","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":698,"r":9,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"15908"},{"n":"John Philip Cunliffe","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":318,"r":10,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"15904"}]},{"ward":"Newton-le-Willows West","seats":3,"turnout_pct":null,"results_url":"https://news.sthelens.gov.uk/localelection2026","candidates":[{"n":"Terry Maguire","p":"Newton-le-Willows Independents","v":1622,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"77387","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/77387/57a9f7c6-091e-492d-9925-4bf4268a6727.png","stmt":"I am standing as a True independent candidate in this year’s local elections in the Earlestown ward. I intend to be a truly independent voice in our town, not one that is constrained by what you must do for your party and having to vote the way you are told and not the way you wish. I feel the time is right to challenge and scrutinise some of the current ruling parties’ decisions and on many occasions, some of their councillors’ attitudes towards their electorate, as it leaves a lot to be desired.  I believe all councillors should use the Nolan principles as their guide and sadly this falls down in many cases.  I certainly believe we need more polite politics in our town.\n\nThe Nolan Principles •\tSelflessness. •\tIntegrity. •\tObjectivity. •\tAccountability. •\tOpenness. •\tHonesty. •\tLeadership.\n\n  I am standing in Earlestown, mostly to listen to residents’ concerns and to be able to represent them fairly and equally, this I believe is the main role of any local councillor. Much too often our local councillors are not visible within their communities and in many cases are not known to the electorate. I wish to change that and be a councillor that people know they can approach for an even and unbiased view to help and mediate their concerns.   I worry about the lack of policing in our area, this concerns many residents greatly, we need more on the beat, particularly at night around known anti-social behavioural hotspots.  If elected I would lobby the new Police & Crime Commissioner on this issue.   I would also arrange regular meetings with local police to discuss residents' worries and concerns.     I am all in favour of the growth and regeneration of our town centre and Town Hall and would be happy to work with all sustainable plans to implement this.  Over the years, there have been many promises for this to happen. Labour have left the Town Hall closed for 13 years, we can now watch to see if their promised plans and allocated monies come to fruition, if they remain i","bd":"1961"},{"n":"Karl Lionel Collier","p":"Newton-le-Willows Independents","v":1426,"r":2,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"90577","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/90577/0051b474-e2a5-4ceb-b9b6-cf86b92bf97b.png"},{"n":"Craig Smith","p":"Newton-le-Willows Independents","v":1148,"r":3,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"90578","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/90578/19db54c2-8afe-4bb6-b89c-b4dc4ea3953a.png"},{"n":"Dave Banks","p":"Labour Party","v":920,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"90152"},{"n":"Peter Thomas Blood","p":"Labour Party","v":900,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"