ates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/126063/28f9f1cd-7699-45a6-a27d-0f5fb1a66f8c.png"},{"n":"Anthony Devanny","p":"Reform UK","v":898,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"134222"},{"n":"Amber Carole Johnson","p":"Green Party","v":758,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"123655","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/123655/4c05337d-ce45-4cad-a932-5436c04631d8.png","stmt":"I have called St Helens home for the past 15 years. Having gone to school and college here, and now as an adult working in the town too, this community means a lot to me.\n\nIt has given me so many opportunities and I feel such a sense of belonging here because of the incredible people I have come to know, I now feel it’s time for me to give back.\n\nAs a working class woman raising a little girl, I feel compelled to be a part of the movement of hope. One that protects people and planet.\n\nI’m standing in Rainford to be a passionate, practical local voice on the council, speaking up for residents who feel overlooked and working to ensure no one in our community is forgotten or left behind.\n\nI believe we can build a fairer, greener future, one where no one is left behind and everyone has a voice.","bd":"1998"},{"n":"Sean Davies","p":"Green Party","v":739,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"123654","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/123654/162a04c8-f02c-4174-8d2a-5088a9fcf17e.png"},{"n":"Richard Jacques","p":"Labour Party","v":495,"r":7,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"134223","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/134223/c8a5f54c-855e-4afd-a924-1a6cb730baca.png"},{"n":"Malcolm Simm","p":"Labour Party","v":437,"r":8,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"134224"}]},{"ward":"Rainhill","seats":3,"turnout_pct":null,"results_url":"https://news.sthelens.gov.uk/localelection2026","candidates":[{"n":"James Tasker","p":"Rainhill Independents","v":2372,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"42244","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/131936/7d07d22f-1ada-406e-aaf3-52194e11b52e.png","stmt":"My name is James Tasker, and I am excited to announce my candidacy as an Independent for St Helens South and Whiston in the upcoming general election.\n\nAs many of you know, I have served Rainhill as an Independent councillor for the last six years. I have always been deeply committed to fighting for our communities and ensuring our voices are heard.\n\nToday, I am taking this commitment a step further. Our community needs a representative in Parliament who is not bound by party politics but is dedicated to addressing our real issues.\n\nI am running as an Independent candidate because I believe St Helens and Whiston deserve an independent voice—someone who prioritises our residents’ needs and interests above all else.\n\nAs a councillor, I have seen the difference that dedicated, community-focused leadership can make. From advocating for better local services and improved infrastructure to supporting our schools and healthcare facilities, my focus has always been making our community a better place to live. I am proud of our progress together, but much work still needs to be done.","tw":"\"Tasker4MP\"","url":"\"https://james-tasker.co.uk/\""},{"n":"Donna Greaves","p":"Rainhill Independents","v":2113,"r":2,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"49972","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/49972/b53aa111-899e-4cba-b399-9db9df08aa1f.png","tw":"\"Donna4Rainhill\""},{"n":"James Dunn","p":"Rainhill Independents","v":2095,"r":3,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"126064","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/126064/46a28911-d3f6-4dcf-b84a-db9e79681463.png"},{"n":"Neil Peter Conway","p":"Reform UK","v":806,"r":4,"e":